# Flutter App Rules

- Read `docs/standards/design/accessibility-testing.md` §4.3 for Flutter accessibility.
- Read `docs/standards/design/visual-standards.md` for visual hierarchy.
- Read `docs/standards/design/motion-design.md` for animation patterns.

## Design Tokens
- Use `HUTokens` constants from `lib/tokens.dart` (or equivalent).
- Typography: Nunito Sans as Avenir fallback. Use Material 3 type scale.
- Colors: `Theme.of(context).colorScheme.*` — never hardcoded hex.
- Spacing: token-based, never raw pixel values.

## Architecture
- Gateway connection via `GatewayClient` (JSON-RPC over WebSocket).
- Lazy screen loading (switch, not IndexedStack) for performance.
- `const` constructors wherever possible.
- `RepaintBoundary` on expensive list widgets.

## Accessibility
- `Semantics(header: true)` on screen titles.
- `Semantics(label:, button: true)` on icon-only buttons.
- `ExcludeSemantics` on decorative elements.
- Test with platform screen readers.
